      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/description": [
      {
        "@value": "\n  <p>An abbreviation for a unit is a short ASCII string that is used in place of the full name for the unit in contexts where non-ASCII characters would be problematic,\n   or where using the abbreviation will enhance readability. \n  When a power of abase unit needs to be expressed, such as squares this can be done using abbreviations rather than symbols. \n  For example, <em>sq ft</em> means <em>square foot</em>, and <em>cu ft</em> means <em>cubic foot</em>.\n  </p>",
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy": [
      {
        "@id": "http://qudt.org/schema/qudt"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "abbreviation"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range": [
      {
        "@id": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "_:autos318",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxCardinality": [
      {
        "@value": "1",
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty": [
      {
        "@id": "http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/deprecatedInVersion"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "_:autos319",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxCardinality": [
      {
        "@value": "1",
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty": [
      {
        "@id": "http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/id"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/id",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty",
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"
    ],
    "http://purl.org/dc/terms/description": [
      {
        "@value": "\n  <p>The \"qudt:id\" is an identifier string that uniquely identifies a QUDT concept. \n  The identifier is constructed using a prefix. \n  For example, units are coded using the pattern: \"UCCCENNNN\", where \"CCC\" is a numeric code or a category\n   and \"NNNN\" is a digit string for a member element of that category. \n  </p>\n  <p>For scaled units there may be an addition field that has the format \"QNN\" where \"NN\" is a digit string representing\n   an exponent power, and \"Q\" is a qualifier that indicates with the code \"P\" that the power is a positive decimal exponent,\n   or the code \"N\" for a negative decimal exponent, or the code \"B\" for binary positive exponents.\n  </p>",
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy": [
      {
        "@id": "http://qudt.org/schema/qudt"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "qudt id"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range": [
      {
        "@id": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "_:autos320",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#allValuesFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty": [
      {
        "@id": "http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/abbreviation"
      }
    ]
  },
