    ],
    "http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/plainTextDescription": [
      {
        "@value": "\n  Scales, or scales of measurement (or categorization) provide ways of quantifying measurements, values and other enumerated values according to a normative frame of reference. \n  Four different types of scales are typically used. \n  These are interval, nominal, ordinal and ratio scales.\n  "
      }
